5. Learnings & Key Points
This project taught me how important it is to use functions to break the code into small, reusable blocks. This was especially useful for tasks that happen repeatedly, like displaying the menu or taking an order line-item.

It also gave me good practice in organizing data using nested if/else statements. I used these to guide the user through specific choicesâ€”for example, first selecting a general category (like "Veg") and then drilling down to a specific cuisine (like "Korean food").
